commentTextItems.html: back of a length and outside the off, Dravid drives beautifully through the covers off the back foot and that brings this game to a close

commentPostTextItems.html: India have won by 6 wickets with just 4 balls to spare
oops our commentator seems to begwetting a bit excited here
India won of course by 4 wickets and not 6 wickets as earlier mentioned

That is the end of our coverage from Bulawayo. We leave you with memories of a day when Ganguly regained his form with an innings of 85, where Dravid made a sparkling unbeaten 72 and Grant Flower shocked everyone by picking 4 wickets in the space of just
For more indepth analysis, features, photographs, articles and everything else you could possibly want, just log on to: http://www.cricinfo.com/link_to_database/ARCHIVE/2001/OD_TOURNEYS/CCC-ZIM/
See you all at Bulawayo on Saturday, 30 June
Mail all your comments about coverage to comms@cricinfo.com we appreciate all feedback
Till the 30th of June, a very Good Night to you all

stories.title: 3rd Match, India v Zimbabwe, Coca Cola Cup, Statistical Highlights
stories.summary: It was the 1730th ODI in cricket history

stories.title: Ganguly thanks everyone
stories.summary:
Indian captain Saurav Ganguly, who ended his recent run-drought with a
painstaking 85 to lay the foundation for India's four-wicket win
against Zimbabwe in Bulawayo on Wednesday, thanked one and all for
supporting him through his lean period

stories.title: Ganguly, Dravid star as India race to victory
stories.summary:
Zimbabwe probably forfeited their place in the Coca Cola Cup final
when they lost to India by four wickets at the Queen's Sports Club in
Bulawayo on Wednesday
